#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/dust_mephit.md:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Armor Class** 12    \n"
"**Hit Points** 17 (5d6)    \n"
"**Speed** 30 ft., fly 30 ft. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/dust_mephit.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| STR     | DEX     | CON     | INT     | WIS     | CHA     |\n"
"|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|\n"
"| 5 (−3)  | 14 (+2) | 10 (+0) | 9 (−1)  | 11 (+0) | 10 (+0) |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/dust_mephit.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Skills** Perception +2, Stealth +4    \n"
"**Damage Vulnerabilities.** fire    \n"
"**Damage Immunities** poison    \n"
"**Condition Immunities** poisoned    \n"
"**Senses** darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 12    \n"
"**Languages** Auran, Terran    \n"
"**Challenge** 1/2 (100 XP) \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/dust_mephit.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Death Burst.** When the mephit dies, it explodes in a burst of dust. Each "
"creature within 5 feet of it must then succeed on a DC 10 Constitution "
"saving throw or be blinded for 1 minute. A blinded creature can repeat the "
"saving throw on each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a "
"success.    \n"
"**Innate Spellcasting (1/Day).** The mephit can innately cast **_sleep_**, "
"requiring no material components. Its innate spellcasting ability is "
"Charisma. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/dust_mephit.md:29
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"### Actions    \n"
"**Claws.** _Melee Weapon Attack:_ +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one "
"creature. _Hit:_ 4 (1d4 + 2) slashing damage.    \n"
"**Blinding Breath (Recharge 6).** The mephit exhales a 15- foot cone of "
"blinding dust. Each creature in that area must succeed on a DC 10 Dexterity "
"saving throw or be blinded for 1 minute. A creature can repeat the saving "
"throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a "
"success.\n"
msgstr ""
